{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"slug":1,"metadata":2,"images":98,"html":186,"xml":234},"ISic001830",{"file":1,"uri":1,"title":3,"status":4,"editions":6,"editionAuthor":17,"type":18,"support":22,"objectType":23,"material":27,"condition":33,"dimensions":34,"layoutDesc":45,"handNote":52,"date":66,"places":71,"geo":81,"country":76,"provenance":73,"provenanceFound":85,"provenanceGeo":93,"provenanceObserved":94,"provenanceLost":17,"graphics":98,"region":105,"settlement":78,"repository":106,"idno":121,"textLang":123,"bibliographyEdition":127,"bibliographyDiscussion":141,"citation":144,"tmNumber":33,"facsimile":165,"letterHeights":166,"publications":171,"zotero":173,"keywords":175,"lettering_types":185},"Building inscription of Martinianos",{"_":5},"draft",[7,9,11,13,15],{"type":8},"TM",{"type":10},"EDR",{"type":12},"EDH",{"type":14},"EDCS",{"type":16},"PHI",null,{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"building","#function.building","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/.html","9 fragments of a white marble plaque. The fragments consist of two joining sets, with an unquantifiable gap between them. Two fragments join to preserve part of the left margin; seven fragments join to preserve part of the upper and right margin, including the upper right corner; the lower margin is not preserved. The total width of the preserved fragments is 86cm, therefore the original total width was greater; the maximum preserved height is 35cm (so the total height was greater); thickness is 3 cm.",{"_":24,"ana":25,"ref":26},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":28,"ana":29,"type":30,"subtype":31,"ref":32},"marble","#material.inorganic.stone.metamorphic_rock.marble","stone.marble","unverified","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",[35,39,42],{"_":36,"unit":37,"dimension":38},"35 (preserved minimum)","cm","height",{"_":40,"unit":37,"dimension":41},"86 (preserved minimum)","width",{"_":43,"unit":37,"dimension":44},"3","depth",{"layout":46},{"p":47,"rs":48,"damage":33},"Traces of three lines of ancient Greek are preserved, with guidelines above and below; upper, left and right margins are partially preserved. The text appears to maintain a consistent margin on the left, but not on the right.",{"_":49,"ana":50,"ref":51},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":53,"dimensions":54},"Tall, regular, narrow letters, v-cut, with small serifs on the termination of strokes. Small deep triangular interpuncts. Alpha has broken bar; epsilon tall, narrow, with equal short horizontals; theta and omicron are rhomboid; mu has vertical first and last, with the diagonals starting below the top and only desencing to the mid-point; nu is similar; rho has small curved, closed loop; sigma is lunate but rectilinear, with very short horizontals.",[55,62],{"type":56,"l":57,"from":58,"to":59,"h":60,"unit":61,"atLeast":60,"atMost":60},"letterHeight","Line 1-2","line1","line2","110","mm",{"type":63,"l":64,"from":58,"to":59,"h":65,"unit":61,"atLeast":65,"atMost":65},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","20",{"_":67,"notBefore":68,"notAfter":69,"evidence":70},"Dated by reference to Flavius Martinianos, consularis of Sicily between 352 and 358 CE (Soraci)",352,358,"prosopography",[72,77],{"_":73,"type":74,"ref":75,"region":76},"Agrigentum","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462086","Sicilia",{"_":78,"type":79,"ref":80,"region":76},"Agrigento","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/6541860",[82],[83,84],37.32084,13.58876,{"_":86,"type":87,"subtype":88,"when":89,"geo":90},"The principal fragment was found during excavation of a lime kiln in room d1 of casa IIC of the quartiere ellenistico romano of Agrigento; it was subsequently reconnected with fragments found in the same approximate location in the 1950s.","found","discovered","2013",[91,92],37.297649,13.591579,[91,92],{"_":95,"type":96,"subtype":97,"geo